    ['Time Slips Away'] = {
        id = 44,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Pashhow Marshlands',
        start_pos = 'K-6',
        description = 'Mission Orders: A distraught Cait Sith has enlisted your help to recover the punch bug, an indispensable little critter that escaped her grasp in a moment of distraction. Your best bet is to search for it in dark, damp places. Cramped, moist environs.',
        reward = '[Key Item] Bottled punch bug',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Glimmer of Life'},
        next = {'When Wills Collide'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Trade a Punch Bug to the Veridical Conflux in Grauberg (S) at (F-5) for a cutscene.\n   - Punch Bugs drop from Lou Carcolhs, Ancient Quadavs, Gold Quadavs, Vajra Quadavs in Pashhow Marshlands (S); and Ancient Quadavs, Gold Quadavs, Vajra Quadavs in Beadeaux (S).\n2. You will obtain a [Key Item] Bottled punch bug after trading with the Veridical Conflux.\n   - The C.A (Campaign Arbiter) Warp will bring you closest to reach Witchfire Glen for this objective if you have little to no progress with Voidwatch.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Traitor in the Midst'] = {
        id = 17,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Beaucedine Glacier',
        start_pos = 'J-8',
        description = 'Cait Sith Naoi is convinced a traitor walks among her kin.  Unmasking the turncoat requires that you attach a "shadow bug" to each of the Cait Siths scattered  throughout the Beaucedine Glacier.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Northland Exposure'},
        next = {'Betrayal at Beaucedine'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'You must find and plant a [Key Item] Shadow bug on 5 Cait Siths scattered throughout Beaucedine Glacier (S).\nAt each tower you will be required to complete a mini game to attach the [Key Item] Shadow bug to a Cait Sith by clicking the Regal Pawprints.\n\n\nNote: Order does not matter, in this walkthrough they are listed bottom-to-top. If you use the Survival Guide, reverse the order. Be mindful that there are several other Regal Pawprints in the area used for following missions.\n\nYou have three tries to complete each mini game.  If you fail, simply try again. You do not need to zone.\n1. Cait Sith Coig is at the tower at (J-8).  You must hit it with a blow dart to attach the bug.\n   - Moves back and forth in a seemingly random pattern.\nNote: Easiest way to win the 3 following \'Red Light, Green Light\' minigames is to wait till Cait Sith\'s head is turned 45-degrees to move.\nThe Cait Sith will turn at entirely random intervals. When she turns at a 45-degree angle however, the next turn will always be facing away. This is the very best time to move. You can move 2-4 (even 5 if you\'re risky) times when she finally does a 45-degree turn. This will often be accompanied by a frustrated scribble "thought bubble" which is a good visual indicator that you can quickly take 1-2 moves in safety. Cait Sith can cycle through numerous quick turns, so it is best to wait for sideways 45 degree turn to advance.\n\nIf you are using the FastCS addon, unload it before initiating this minigame, as it will make it substantially more difficult.\n2. Cait Sith Seachd is at the tower at (I-7).  You must direct Lilisette in a game of \'Red Light, Green\' Light until she is close enough to plant the bug.\n   - If you see Lilisette put her hands on her hips it means she will move 2 steps instead of one the next time you tell her to move.\n3. Cait Sith Ceithir is at the tower at (G-9).  You must direct Portia in a game of \'Red Light, Green Light\' until she is close enough to plant the bug.\n   - If Portia begins to panic she will be much slower the next time you tell her to move.\n4. Cait Sith Aon is at the tower at (H-8).  You play a game of \'Red Light, Green\' Light in first person view.\n   - This is the tower the Campaign Arbiter will teleport you to.\n5. Cait Sith Tri is at the tower at (F-7). Here you are transformed into a baby chocobo and have to sneak up on Cait Sith Tri.\n   - You only have 1 minute until your disguise wears off.\n   - You have the option of either chirping or wiggling your butt to get the Cait Sith\'s attention.\n   - Once the Cait Sith is close enough, a third menu option "Stun!" will appear.  Use the stun option to complete this mini game.\n\nOnce you have planted a bug on all 5 Cait Sith\'s, check the Regal Pawprints at (H-10). These pawprints are not at the base of the tower like the others.  They are under a large broken tree branch near the tower.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['When Wills Collide'] = {
        id = 45,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Walk of Echoes',
        start_pos = 'F-5',
        description = 'Mission Orders: To regain a foothold in the struggle and ensure Lilisette\'s rebirth, you must confront whatever darkness lies in wait at the Walk of Echoes.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Time Slips Away'},
        next = {'Whispers of Dawn'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Enter Walk of Echoes from the Veridical Conflux in Grauberg (S) at (F-5).\n2. Examine the Ornate Door north of the Veridical Conflux in the Walk of Echoes for a cutscene, examine it again to enter a BC.\n3. Your opponents in this BC are the Spitewardens.\n   - The first Spitewarden is a MNK who uses a staff.  Can use Hundred Fists, has a special weaponskill called Forlorn Strike.\n   - The second Spitewarden is a PLD.  Can use Invincible, casts Banish and Banishga spells, and shares hate with the third Spitewarden.\n   - The third Spitewarden is a DNC.  Can use trance, and is capable of curing and removing debuffs (such as gravity), and will occasionally cure the second Spitewarden.  Also has a special gaze attack with a Doom effect, it can be avoided by turning away.\n   - The fourth Spitewarden does not seem to have a job, but will use a weapon that matches the person who starts the BC, and has access to all weaponskills for that weapon, also has an ability at low HP called Essence Jack that will lower your statuses, inflict terror, and give a damage boost.\n     - A good strategy is to use gravity to kite the Spitewardens while DDs deal with them one at a time.  If you are going to kite, it is a good idea to deal with the third Spitewarden first, since DNC is capable of dispelling Gravity, although the second Spitewarden will assist.\n     - The BC is won when all four Spitewardens are defeated, should you be defeated, you will have to obtain another Punch Bug to try again.\n4. This fight is easily won at iLevel and you may not even need Trusts to help.',
        notes = nil,
    },
